    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! You have seriously got to see this beauty. It\u2019s in absolutely incredible shape\u2014honestly, it looks and drives like it just rolled off the showroom floor! I\u2019ve babied this car since day one, and it really shows in every little detail. If you\u2019re looking for that perfect, like-new feel without the brand-new price tag, this is definitely the one for you. Swing by and take a look, you\u2019re going to love it!",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 16
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains its factory-spec thermal management and vacuum line routing, ensuring the complex sequential transition remains seamless. The chassis is remarkably rigid, preserving the original 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension geometry. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential, with no evidence of synchro wear or drivetrain lash. The exterior finish and interior appointments are flawless, reflecting a life of climate-controlled storage and meticulous preventative maintenance. An uncompromising specimen for the discerning rotary purist.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 16
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "2021 model. Single owner. Garage kept. Zero accidents. Full service history available. Showroom condition.",
      "price": 46000.0,
